Create an Rmd file for the report

GenerateRmd.Rd

Create an Rmd file for the report

GenerateRmd(
  usexlsform = FALSE,
  form = NULL,
  ds = NULL,
  surveyConsent = NULL,
  reportingColumns = NULL,
  uniqueID = NULL,
  dates = NULL,
  surveyDate = NULL,
  startDataCollection = NULL,
  dateFormat = NULL,
  minimumSurveyDuration = NULL,
  minimumSurveyDurationByIndividual = NULL,
  sdval = NULL,
  HouseholdSize = NULL,
  deleteIsInterviewCompleted = NULL,
  deleteIsInterviewWithConsent = NULL,
  correctIsInterviewInTheCorrectSite = NULL,
  deleteIsInterviewAtTheSamplePoint = NULL,
  deleteIsUniqueIDMissing = NULL,
  deleteIsUniqueIDDuplicated = NULL,
  deleteIsSurveyOnMoreThanADay = NULL,
  deleteIsSurveyEndBeforeItStarts = NULL,
  deleteIsSurveyStartedBeforeTheAssessment = NULL,
  deleteIsSurveyMadeInTheFuture = NULL,
  deleteIsInterviewTooShort = NULL,
  deleteIsInterviewTooShortForTheHouseholdSize = NULL,
  enumeratorID = NULL,
  enumeratorcheck = FALSE,
  otherPattern = NULL,
  adminBoundaries = NULL,
  dsSite = NULL,
  dsCoordinates = NULL,
  adminBoundariesSite = NULL,
  sampledPoints = NULL,
  buffer = NULL,
  questionsSurveyBigValues = NULL,
  questionsSurveySmallValues = NULL,
  questionsEnumeratorIsLazy = NULL,
  sampleSizeTable = NULL,
  sampleSizeTableSite = NULL,
  sampleSizeTableTarget = NULL,
  sampleSizeTableAvailable = NULL,
  consentForValidSurvey = NULL
)

Arguments

usexlsform

do not know but have to be documented
form

do not know but have to be documented
ds

dataset as a data.frame object
surveyConsent

name as a string of the field in the dataset where the survey consent is stored
reportingColumns

columns as a list of string name from the dataset you want in the result (c('col1','col2',...))
uniqueID

name as a string of the field in the dataset where the unique ID is stored
dates

fields as a list of string where the survey start and end date is stored (c('start_date','end_date'))
surveyDate

name as a string of the field in the dataset where the date of the survey is stored
startDataCollection

date as a string of the first day of data collection ('yyyy-mm-dd')
dateFormat

format as a string used for the date ('%m/%d/%Y')
minimumSurveyDuration

minimum acceptable survey duration as integer in minutes
minimumSurveyDurationByIndividual

minimum acceptable survey duration for one indifidual as integer in minutes
sdval

number of standard deviation for which the data within is considered as acceptable
HouseholdSize

name as a string of the field in the dataset where the household size is stored
deleteIsInterviewCompleted

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isInterviewCompleted function
deleteIsInterviewWithConsent

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isInterviewWithConsent function
correctIsInterviewInTheCorrectSite

correction action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isInterviewInTheCorrectSite function
deleteIsInterviewAtTheSamplePoint

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isInterviewAtTheSamplePoint function
deleteIsUniqueIDMissing

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isUniqueIDMissing function
deleteIsUniqueIDDuplicated

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isUniqueIDDuplicated function
deleteIsSurveyOnMoreThanADay

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isSurveyOnMoreThanADay function
deleteIsSurveyEndBeforeItStarts

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isSurveyEndBeforeItStarts function
deleteIsSurveyStartedBeforeTheAssessment

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isSurveyStartedBeforeTheAssessment function
deleteIsSurveyMadeInTheFuture

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isSurveyMadeInTheFuture function
deleteIsInterviewTooShort

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isInterviewTooShort function
deleteIsInterviewTooShortForTheHouseholdSize

delete action to be done as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE) for isInterviewTooShortForTheHouseholdSize function
enumeratorID

name as a string of the field in the dataset where the enumerator ID is stored
enumeratorcheck

specify if the report has to be displayed for each enumerator or not as a boolean (TRUE/FALSE)
otherPattern

pattern as string to identify the fields containing others values ('_other$')
adminBoundaries

dataset containing the shapefile - Regardless the projection used for the shapefile, it is transformed to WGS84
dsSite

name as a string of the field in the dataset where the site is stored
dsCoordinates

columns as a list of string name from the dataset where the GPS coordinates are stored (c('Long','Lat'))
adminBoundariesSite

name as a string of the field in the shapefile where the site is stored
sampledPoints

dataset containing the shapefile - Regardless the projection used for the shapefile, it is transformed to WGS84
buffer

value as an integer in meter to determine the buffer from a sampled point which is acceptable
questionsSurveyBigValues

columns as a list of string name from the dataset you want to check against (c(col1=x,col2=x,...))
questionsSurveySmallValues

columns as a list of string name from the dataset you want to check against (c(col1=x,col2=x,...))
questionsEnumeratorIsLazy

columns as a list of string name from the dataset you want to check against (c(col1=x,col2=x,...))
sampleSizeTable

sampling frame as a data.frame object
sampleSizeTableSite

name as a string of the field in the sampling frame where the site is stored
sampleSizeTableTarget

name as a string of the field where the target number of survey is stored in the sampling frame
sampleSizeTableAvailable

name as a string of the field where the number of points generated is stored in the sampling frame
consentForValidSurvey

consent value for the valid surveys as string

Value

vignette file

Author

Yannick Pascaud, Edouard Legoupil

Examples

if (FALSE) {
ds <- HighFrequencyChecks::sample_dataset

survey_consent <- "survey_consent"
reportingcol <- c("enumerator_id","X_uuid")
UniqueID <- "X_uuid"

## Setting dates
dates <- c("survey_start","end_survey")
surveydate <- "survey_date"
start_collection <- "2018-11-11"
dateformat <- "%m/%d/%Y"
minduration <- 30
sdval <- 2
HHSize <-"consent_received.respondent_info.hh_size"


## Setting action on dataset
delete <- FALSE
correct <- FALSE

## Setting enumerator
enumeratorID <- "enumerator_id"
enumeratorcheck <- FALSE
otherpattern <- "_other$"

## Setting linked geodata
adm <- HighFrequencyChecks::admin
ds_site <- "union_name"
ds_coord <- c("X_gps_reading_longitude","X_gps_reading_latitude")
adm_site <- "Union"
pts <- HighFrequencyChecks::SamplePts
buff <- 10

## setting questions to check
questions <-c("consent_received.food_security.spend_food",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_medication",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_education",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_fix_shelter",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_clothing",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_hygiene",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_fuel",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_hh_items",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_transport",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_communication",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_tobacco",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_rent",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_debts",
  "consent_received.food_security.spend_other")
value <- 25000
minnbanswers <- 3


## setting sampling plan
sf <- HighFrequencyChecks::SampleSize
dssite <- "union_name"
sfsite <- "Union"
survey_consent <- "survey_consent"
sftarget <- "SS"
sfnbpts <- "TotPts"
formul <- c("done-no-not_eligible-delete",
"done-no-not_eligible-deleted-SS")
colorder <- c("site","SS","Provisio","done","not_eligible",
 "no","deleted","yes","final","variance")

GenerateRmd(ds,
  survey_consent,
  reportingcol,
  UniqueID,
  dates,
  surveydate,
  start_collection,
  dateformat,
  minduration,
  sdval,
  HHSize,
  delete,
  correct,
  enumeratorID,
  enumeratorcheck,
  otherpattern,
  adm,
  ds_site,
  ds_coord,
  adm_site,
  pts,
  buff,
  questions,
  value,
  minnbanswers,
  sf, dssite,
  sfsite,
  sftarget,
  sfnbpts,
  formul,
  colorder)
}
